; DOMAIN: number-theory [CLOSED, derived 2026-07-24] ; Claim: for pairwise-coprime moduli, the system of congruences has a unique solution mod their product (Chinese Remainder Theorem). ; Structure: (moduli m1..mk pairwise-coprime) (residues r1..rk). ; Result: exists unique x mod (prod m_i) with x = r_i (mod m_i); ring iso Z/(prod m_i) = product of Z/m_i. ; Minimal: pairwise-coprimality => CRT ring isomorphism (splitting). ; Bridge: decomposition/factoring principle — mirrors product-of-measures independence and category product decomposition. (= (solve-crt $sys) (reconstruct (residues $sys) (moduli $sys)))